					<description><![CDATA[<p>Hippo Harvest Raises $30M to Scale Robotic Greenhouse Production Hippo Harvest has raised $30 million in Series C funding to expand its robotics-powered greenhouse operations and increase production of organic</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/hippo-harvest-raises-30m-to-expand-robotic-greenhouse-farming/" data-wpel-link="internal">Hippo Harvest Raises $30M to Expand Robotic Greenhouse Farming</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Hippo Harvest Raises $30M to Scale Robotic Greenhouse Production</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hippo Harvest has raised $30 million in Series C funding to expand its robotics-powered greenhouse operations and increase production of organic leafy greens. The funding round was led by Cox Farms, North America&#8217;s largest greenhouse operator.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The California-based company plans to use the capital to build a new 30-acre greenhouse facility in Hollister, subject to regulatory approval. The investment will also support the development of its next-generation robotic growing system and speed up the commercial rollout of indoor-grown spinach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hippo Harvest says the expansion will significantly increase its production capacity. It currently operates one acre of greenhouse space and supplies retailers across Northern California and the Pacific Northwest.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports New Crops and Smarter Farming Technology</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new round comes as Hippo Harvest launches its new indoor-grown spinach offering. This marks the latest expansion to the company’s line, following last spring’s debut of its organic butter lettuce product. These together bolster the firm&#8217;s catalog of year-round organic produce.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hippo Harvest leverages their own in-house autonomous mobile robot technology which oversees every part of the planting and growth cycle &#8211; monitoring plants, adjusting levels and picking them for market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These robotic units also relocate plant modules for maximum use of the greenhouses and greater yields. They stated the new system will enhance their manufacturing efficiency, drive down operational expenditures and expedite new plant strains into market. </span></p>
<h2><b>Retail Expansion Builds on Climate-Resilient Agriculture</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203493" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203493" class="size-full wp-image-203493" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Hippo-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI-powered robotic greenhouses producing organic vegetables year-round and supplying retailers through a climate-resilient agricultural network." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203493" class="wp-caption-text">Climate-resilient greenhouse farming powered by robotics and machine learning is expanding retail distribution, enabling reliable year-round organic food production while supporting sustainable growth across regional and national markets. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hippo Harvest, founded in 2019, grows greenhouse vegetables along with organic field crops. That gives retailers more options and a reliable supply throughout the year regardless of weather, Chief Executive Officer Eitan Marder-Eppstein told Food Dive.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Currently, the farm distributes products through retailers such as Sprouts, Haggen and Gus’s Community Markets. The company said it intends to use the capital to boost distribution throughout the West Coast and to grow its national retail presence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Marder-Eppstein called the investment round a significant milestone for Hippo Harvest. “Through years of investment in our robotics and machine learning systems, we have built a farming operation that can produce consistent, high-quality organic produce in an economically competitive way,” he said.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/oxylabs-raises-130m-to-expand-ai-data-infrastructure-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Oxylabs Raises $130M to Expand AI Data Infrastructure Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Strategic Investor Backs Next Growth Phase</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cox Farms led the round alongside Congruent Ventures, Hawthorne Food Ventures, Collaborative Fund, and Fresh Investment Club. The round brings in the largest cash infusion of any of Hippo Harvest&#8217;s rounds, coming just months after the company closed a $21 million Series B in early 2024. &#8220;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">We believe Hippo Harvest has a very promising business model for indoor farming,&#8221; said Steve Bradley, president of Cox Farms. &#8220;We believe continued innovation is crucial for creating more sustainable and resilient food production systems.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment comes amid a wave of <a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/enthusiasm" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external">enthusiasm</a> for agricultural technologies aimed at making food production more efficient and less harmful to the environment, as a greater portion of investor capital flows to companies developing smart and environmentally conscious farming technologies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/hippo-harvest-raises-30m-to-expand-robotic-greenhouse-farming/" data-wpel-link="internal">Hippo Harvest Raises $30M to Expand Robotic Greenhouse Farming</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
