					<description><![CDATA[<p>Kraken Technology Raises $175M to Scale Autonomous Maritime Defence Kraken Technology has raised $175 million in a Series B funding round to accelerate the development of autonomous maritime defence systems.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kraken-technology-raises-175m-to-expand-maritime-defence-systems/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kraken Technology Raises $175M to Expand Maritime Defence Systems</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Kraken Technology Raises $175M to Scale Autonomous Maritime Defence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kraken Technology has raised $175 million in a Series B funding round to accelerate the development of autonomous maritime defence systems. The funding values the UK-based company at $1 billion, making it one of Europe&#8217;s latest defence technology unicorns.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by DTCP. It also attracted backing from the British Business Bank, NATO Innovation Fund, Rheinmetall, Inocea Group, HICO, Thesiger Capital Group, BOKA Capital, Supernova Invest, Hakluyt Capital, the UK&#8217;s National Security Strategic Investment Fund, SmartCap, Notion Capital and Speedinvest.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fresh capital will support rapid product development and expand Kraken&#8217;s international manufacturing footprint. The company also plans to strengthen production partnerships across key global defence markets.</span></p>
<h2><b>Autonomous Vessels Target Modern Naval Operations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Chief Executive Officer Mal Crease, Kraken Technology develops autonomous uncrewed surface vessels and subsurface platforms for defence, security and commercial customers. Systems operate using lightweight carbon-fibre composites.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its flagship K3 SCOUT platform supports missions including maritime surveillance, logistics, force protection and </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/precision" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">precision</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> strikes. The company also produces the K4 MANTA, a hybrid vessel capable of operating both above and below the water&#8217;s surface for covert operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kraken&#8217;s larger K5 KRAKEN and K7 SABRE platforms are designed for long-endurance missions, anti-submarine warfare and advanced strike capabilities. These modular systems allow operators to adapt vessels quickly for changing mission requirements.</span></p>
<h2><b>Global Partnerships Strengthen Manufacturing Expansion</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203487" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203487" class="size-full wp-image-203487" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Kraken-2.png" alt="Illustration of global defence manufacturing partnerships producing autonomous maritime systems through interconnected shipyards and resilient international supply chains." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203487" class="wp-caption-text">Global manufacturing partnerships are accelerating the deployment of autonomous maritime defence systems, strengthening supply chain resilience and expanding sovereign production capabilities for defence organisations worldwide. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kraken has built manufacturing partnerships with several international defence companies to support local production. These include Rheinmetall in Germany, Anduril Industries in the United States and Inocea&#8217;s Davie Shipbuilding in Canada.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company intends to establish additional manufacturing partnerships across the Middle East and the Indo-Pacific. This strategy is expected to improve supply chain resilience while helping defence customers develop sovereign production capabilities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding follows several major contract wins with the UK Ministry of Defence, NATO partners across Europe and the United States Special Operations Command. Kraken said its autonomous platforms are already supporting operations in active conflict environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer Mal Crease said the investment would accelerate the company&#8217;s international rollout of mission-ready maritime capabilities for NATO allies and defence partners worldwide.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/gim-raises-us20-million-ai-investment-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">GIM Raises US$20 Million to Advance AI Investment Systems</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investment Reflects Growing Demand for Defence Technology</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Global investor interest in defence technology has continued to increase as governments modernise military capabilities. Autonomous systems have become a major focus, particularly across maritime, aerial and land-based operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">DTCP Partner Ole Aguirre said the maritime sector has historically received less investment despite its strategic importance. He added that Kraken has demonstrated an ability to rapidly develop affordable autonomous vessels capable of meeting NATO&#8217;s operational requirements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike many competitors, Kraken combines in-house engineering with manufacturing partnerships rather than building its own shipyards. This model allows the company to expand production more quickly while supporting local industrial capacity in multiple regions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With new funding secured, Kraken plans to accelerate manufacturing, strengthen its technology platform and expand the deployment of autonomous vessels for defence customers around the world.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kraken-technology-raises-175m-to-expand-maritime-defence-systems/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kraken Technology Raises $175M to Expand Maritime Defence Systems</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
